<br>
Tanik is a triggered spawn<br>
<br>
head to eastern wastes and the kael ramp. the way to trigger him is to run up and down the kael ramp. (worked best for me when i ran zig zag). he spawns down towards the bottom of the ramp and is laying on the ground.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;hail Tanik Greskil&quot;<br>
Tanik Greskil says &quot;Outlander! Thank Brell you've found me! I am the last<br>
surviving member of my unit. Our mission was somehow compromised, the bloody<br>
Kromrif knew just where to find us... I can't imagine how they knew. I was<br>
barely able to escape with my life and wandered into a trap here. I am badly<br>
hurt and need your help.&quot;<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;i will help&quot;<br>
Tanik Greskil says &quot;Quickly, give me a vial of Veluim Vapors so I can return<br>
home, I am in desperate need of some attention from our clerics.&quot;<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;what velium vapors&quot;<br>
Tanik Greskil says &quot;Drat! Are you telling me you don't have one with you?<br>
Run back to Thurgadin at once and speak with Frundle, she can make you one.<br>
I will do what I can to stay alive. I may need to move about a bit to keep<br>
from being discovered. Hurry now outlander, you're my only hope.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
so now you have to run back to thurgadin. Frundle can be found in one of the three buildings across from the paladin guild (near the library).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;what velium vapors?&quot;<br>
Frundle Frenkler says &quot;Ahh, you come seeking my family recipe? After all<br>
you've done for our people it's the least I can do. First you must fashion a<br>
velium vial, then combine the vial with two small pieces of velium in this<br>
jar. That's all there is to it. Please keep the recipe a secret.&quot;<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;what velium vial?&quot;<br>
Frundle Frenkler says &quot;I'm no potter mind you, but if I remember correctly<br>
it's a small brick of velium, three crystalline silks, and two glass shards.<br>
Then you'll have to finish up by firing it in a kiln with a high quality<br>
firing sheet.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
she will give you a 4 slot purifier. it is a container, so you will need an open inventory slot.<br>
<br>
now you need to collect your ingedients. go to CC. everything you need is there. hunt the miners up top for the small pieces and small bricks of velium. then drop (make sure you have lev!) down to the bottom, run through the dorf town, and into the hall with the velium crawlers, spiderlings, and webmasters. the spiderlings die in one nuke (68<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . the crawlers die in one nuke and one ES dot (688+300=around 1k HP). webmasters are tougher and i avoided them. in about an hour, i had a stack of these and gated out.<br>
<br>
head back to thurgadin. go in the bank. the vendor on the very left sells crystal shards and HQ firing sheets. buy 2 crystal shards and 1 HQ firing sheet.<br>
<br>
go click on the pottery wheel in the bank. put the items in like this:<br>
<br>
crystalline silk<br>
crystalline silk<br>
crystalline silk<br>
glass shard<br>
glass shard<br>
small brick of velium<br>
<br>
do not stack the silks. also, even though all other pottery i've done always requires a water flask, do not use one. i tried and it didn't combine. so NO WATER FLASK! i'm around 100 in pottery and it was not trivial.<br>
<br>
you will get an unfired velious vial.<br>
<br>
right next to the pottery wheel is the kiln. combine the vial you just made with a high quality firing sheet. this will produce a velious vial. it was trivial at 100.<br>
<br>
<br>
now, open that purifier box that you got and put in the vial, and 2 small pieces of velium. make sure they are not stacked.<br>
<br>
small piece of velium<br>
small piece of velium<br>
velious vial<br>
<br>
hit combine and you will have a vial of velium vapors. this looks like it can be used by characters as well. it has one charge of &quot;thurgadin gate&quot; and apparently will gate you to thurgadin, although i didnt try.<br>
<br>
<br>
now run back to eastern wastes and find tanik again. give him the vial of velium vapors and he will thank you and then poof, leaving you a note to deliver to loremaster borannin. go back to thurgadin and turn your woven shawl along with the note to loremaster borannin and you will get faction and your shawl will be updated.<br>
<br>
