<br>
Anyway, I got the deathsquad spawned on me and barely made it out using jboots. Yeah, I guess I was lucky. You can run as fast as the giants IF you strafe run - this kinda makes nagivating impossible though as its hard to see where youre going and next to impossible to steer.<br>
<br>
Anyway, while strafe running I had the external camera on and was was holding the forward and left arrows - I ended up making a huge arc towards the orc fort, minor course adjustment not to run into the walls then I directed myself into the hills there. For any who dont know, hills work to your advantage - mobs seem to move slower over them - well the arc ended up getting me close to GD zone and the quantity of hills there allowed me to put some distance from the deathsquad - so I made it to zone (much to my surprize).<br>
<br>
I basically made a choice - try and run or try and gate - seems I was lucky to chose run and have some fortune with my strafing - my channeling is pretty good, but I was 99% sure that 6 giants beating on me would be too much to channel through.<br>
<br>
My advice is to get a sow - jboots saved me, but without substantial luck I would have been toast <p><font face="verdana" size="2">[60 Sorcerer] <b>Diomedes</b> (High Elf) -The Vagrants- ZONE:ezboard<br>
